    "actions_taken": [
      "Investigation committee formed on January 19, 2024",
      "Recovery operations initiated",
      "Well successfully plugged on February 11, 2024",
      "Casing recovered on February 11, 2024",
      "BSEE issued immediate preservation order for all equipment and casing",
      "Metallurgical testing of casing connections performed"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 18, 2024, while running 22 inch casing on the drillship Noble Stanley Lafosse at GC 478 Well 004, the S-90/MT connection between joints 16 and 17 failed due to cross-threading. When the slips were opened to install anti-rotation keys, 72 joints of casing fell partially into the hole and onto the seafloor, impacting subsea infrastructure. The connection was made up only 1/4 to 3/8 turn instead of the required 1/2 to 3/4 turn, and visual inspection failed to detect a 0.143 inch gap indicating cross-threading. No injuries or environmental impacts occurred, but damages exceeded $15 million.",
    "recommendations": [],
